North (Hudson) River, showing (left to right) piers 78, 77, 76 and 75, off Twelfth Ave., south from West 38th to 35th Streets. Also shown is the skyline of the surrounding area.

title: North (Hudson) River - Piers 78-75.

text:
North on Twelfth Avenue from 35th Street.
March 17, 1929.
P.L. Sperr, Photographer.

September 16, 1935.

(2)
The same, at an earlier date, as seen from the shore. On the left appears a portion of pier 74.
